      "paper_id": "PMC7433060",
      "text_span_id": "background_1",
      "text": "Acromegaly is a rare, chronic and severe disease in which growth hormone (GH) is overproduced mainly due to GH-secreting pituitary.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "meta-analysis",
      "eco_type": "systematic review",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC7433060:background:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC7433060",
      "text_span_id": "background_2",
      "text": "GH circulates and stimulates production of insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF-1) from the liver.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "meta-analysis",
      "eco_type": "systematic review",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC7433060:background:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC7433060",
      "text_span_id": "background_3",
      "text": "SAs, which suppress GH secretion by binding to somatostatin receptors, remain the primary medical treatment option if surgery is not possible or curative.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "meta-analysis",
      "eco_type": "systematic review",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC7433060:background:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC7433060",
      "text_span_id": "background_4",
      "text": "PEG inhibits production of IGF-1 by binding to GH receptors and preventing their dimerization.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "meta-analysis",
      "eco_type": "systematic review",
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
